# Power BI – Data Analytics Dashboard Portfolio

This repository contains my complete dashboard portfolio built for HR Analytics, Customer Behavior Analysis, Financial Monitoring and Operational Performance.  
All charts in this portfolio were generated using Python (matplotlib).  
Each section includes:  
1) Dashboard topic  
2) Professional explanation  
3) Python code used to create the visualization  

These examples demonstrate my ability to analyze data, design KPIs, create business insights and visualize results using industry-standard reporting logic.

---

# 1. HR KPI – Employee Count by Department

## Explanation  
This dashboard shows the total number of employees working in each department: HR, IT, Sales, Finance and Operations.  
It is used in HR analytics to measure workforce distribution, evaluate departmental size, and track organizational structure capacity.

---

# 2. HR KPI – Monthly Turnover Rate (%)

## Explanation  
Turnover rate shows how many employees leave the company each month.  
It is a critical HR metric for understanding retention, workforce stability and organizational climate.  
This dashboard allows managers to detect risky months and turnover spikes.

---

# 3. Customer Analytics – Churn by Region (%)

## Explanation  
Customer churn is the percentage of lost customers.  
This dashboard compares churn rates in five regions: Ankara, İstanbul, İzmir, Bursa and Antalya.  
It is used to identify high-risk markets, customer loss patterns and retention strategies.

---

# 4. Financial Dashboard – Monthly Revenue (TL)

## Explanation  
This dashboard visualizes monthly revenue.  
It helps finance teams monitor income fluctuations, detect growth declines and prepare forecasting (budget planning).  
It is one of the most important visuals in financial reporting.

---

# 5. Operational Dashboard – Delivery Performance

## Explanation  
This dashboard displays the ratio of on-time deliveries vs delayed shipments.  
It is used by logistics and operations teams to monitor efficiency, find bottlenecks, and improve service quality.

---

# Technologies Used
- Power BI  
- Python (matplotlib, pandas, numpy)  
- SQL  
- Excel (Advanced)  

